message.content:
cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper presents physiologically-based models for pupil light reflex and iridal pattern deformation, which are relevant to computer graphics and animation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GR (Computer Graphics), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The models are also based on measured data and described by differential equations, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
